			<h2>Partners</h2>
			<div class="span12">
				<h3>Collaborating For Social Action</h3>
				<p>Ready Set Drop is co-directed by Design Forum/PDX, Eastman Chemical and HTI Water. This partnership is an example of how a successful 					collaboration between designers and manufacturers leads to an important social cause and solution. This joint effort represents a 							primary interest in community well-being and a result that offers simplicity and healthy recovery in a time of confusion and 										disruption.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="span11"><hr size="5px"></div>
			<div class="span3"><%= img '/images/IRD.png' %></div>
			<div class="span8" id="irdtext">
				<p>International Relief and Development is a Washington, D.C.-based, nonprofit NGO responsible for implementing relief, stability, and 						development programs worldwide. IRD will be given the HydroPackTM product for pre-positioning and delivery to disaster-struck 									communities. IRD shares our primary interest in community well-being as together we provide simplicity and healthy 															recovery in a time of confusion and disruption.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="span11"><hr size="5px"></div>
			<div class="span3"><%= img '/images/DFPDX.png' %></div>
			<div class="span8" id="dfpdxtext">
				<p>Design Forum/PDX is a Portland, Oregon-based resource organization that celebrates design. The nonprofit supports creativity at every 					stage from inspiration to final product. By identifying creative opportunities and providing new tools for the design community, Design 					Forum/PDX embodies a pervasive drive to discover, collaborate and exchange ideas. Through this digital media campaign, Design Forum/PDX 					hopes to raise awareness around innovation and development going on within the Portland design community as well as highlight an 								example where successful collaboration between designers and manufacturers has led to an important social cause and solution.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="span11"><hr size="5px"></div>
			<div class="span3"><%= img '/images/HTI.png' %></div>
			<div class="span8" id="htitext">
				<p>HTI Water manufactures the HydroPack with a nutrient powder inside that produces an osmotic pressure that naturally draws water in 					through the membrane. This filtration process (known as forward osmosis) is identical to the process plants use to pull water into 							their roots. HTI’s exciting design represents the safest and most reliable mobile water filtration system available.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="span11"><hr size="5px"></div>
			<div class="span3" id="Eastmanlogo"><%= img '/images/Eastman.png' %></div>
			<div class="span8" id="eastmantext">
				<p>Eastman Chemical has developed the HydroPack’s unique cellulose membrane that can be permeated only by pure water. The paper-thin 						barrier blocks dirt, bacteria, viruses and other contaminants with a success rate that exceeds EPA standards for water purification. 						Once water is drawn in, the HydroPack’s protective membrane eliminates the possibility of recontamination. This brilliant material 							innovation is essential in the HydroPack’s innovative filtration process.</p>
			</div>
